  Page-count trick\par
  Picture books run in multiples of 4 (signature printing). 24, 28, 32, 36. 32 is the sweet spot \emdash  enough room for a proper story, low enough print cost for pricing flexibility.\par
  Layout planning for 32 pages\par
  pp 1-2     title page + copyright\par
  pp 3-4     dedication + opening spread\par
  pp 5-28    story (12 spreads)\par
  pp 29-30   closing spread + refrain\par
  pp 31-32   "about the Mooshus" + about authors\par
  Critical gotcha\par
  KDP requires single pages, not spreads, but you design in spreads. Workflow: lay out as spreads in Affinity/Procreate/InDesign \f3\u8594? export as individual left/right pages \u8594? combine into one PDF. Faces and\par
  important elements need to stay 0.5" from the center gutter or they'll disappear into the binding.\par
  ---\par
  3. Synthesis \u8594? Execution Plan\par
  What the analysis tells us to do\par
  From the bestseller pattern analysis, your winning stack is:\par
  \f1\u9614?\f4  Transformation world (#6) + Named character (#5) + Rhyming refrain (#2) + Emotional anchor (#3)\par
  This stacks exactly like Llama Llama and Little Blue Truck \emdash  which are the two strongest comparable series at your realistic scale.\par
  Execution roadmap (first 6 months)\par
  Month 1 \emdash  Bible + Pilot\par
  - Complete the character bible template above\par
  - Pick one of the three hook sentences from the last message (my bet: memory-return hook)\par
  - Girlfriend tests 3 hook pitches aloud with kids. Pick the winner by what kids repeat back.\par
  - You produce character sheets for core 3 + one environment key-piece\par
  Month 2 \emdash  Book 1 script + storyboard\par
  - She drafts the story (aim 400 words, 12 spreads)\par
  - Read aloud 10 times to 10 different kids \emdash  cut anything that loses attention\par
  - You thumbnail all 12 spreads at postage-stamp size first\par
  Month 3 \emdash  Start posting content\par
  - Launch IG/TikTok account with character reveals + process\par
  - Post 3\'d7 week: character art, her reading drafts to kids, sketches\par
  - Goal: 500 followers before book 1 releases (totally doable in 90 days with consistent posting)\par
  Month 4 \emdash  Illustrate book 1\par
  - Full color art, one spread per week = 12 weeks... too slow. Compress: finishing 2 spreads/week = 6 weeks.\par
  - Keep posting WIP the whole time\par
  Month 5 \emdash  Layout, proof, polish\par
  - Lay out in Affinity Publisher (free-ish) or Canva Pro ($15/mo)\par
  - Order 1 KDP author proof (~$5\endash 7)\par
  - Fix everything the proof reveals (colors always shift in print)\par
  Month 6 \emdash  Launch\par
  - Publish paperback + Kindle same day\par
  - Price: paperback ~$9.99, Kindle $3.99\par
  - Launch week: ask your 500 followers + her caregiver network to buy + honestly review\par
  - Day 30: free Kindle promo to spike rankings\par
  Ideas for the first four books (memory-return hook)\par
  1. "Mooshu and the Rain That Remembered" \emdash  Mooshu wakes with a memory of a nest. Must find whose. (pilot \emdash  establishes world)\par
  2. "The Lantern Mooshu" \emdash  new Mooshu wakes with a memory of being scared in the dark. (theme: comfort)\par
  3. "Mooshu and the Mender's Song" \emdash  a memory of a broken thing being fixed. (theme: repair/hope)\par
  4. "The Mooshu Who Forgot" \emdash  a Mooshu wakes with no memory at all. (theme: identity/belonging \emdash  strongest emotional hit)\par
